HEADWORD: Convexity
<hw>Con*vex"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Convexities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[L.
<ets>convexitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>convexit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The state of being convex; the exterior surface of a convex body;
roundness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A smooth, uniform <qex>convexity</qex> and rotundity of a
globe.</q> <rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convexly</ent>⟦br⟧
